 The City Diary

 The Centre has released a grant of Rs 8 crore to the state government for developing the runway at Behala Flying Club, the country?s oldest flying institute, transport minister Subhas Chakraborty said in the Assembly on Monday.

 e was replying to a question asked by Trinamul Congress MLA Partha Chatterjee. The Centre, however, has laid down a condition that funds for electrification and water supply would have to be provided by the state government.

 he minister said the process of selecting the private partner that will run the flying institute was on. ?A number of companies are willing to run the institute. The tender process will be over soon,? he added.

 The School of Tropical Medicine has confirmed four more dengue cases. Chief municipal health officer Deb Dwaipayan Chattopadhyay said on Monday that two each are from Howrah and North 24-Parganas.

 A 30-year-old man was found dead on Raja Rajkrishna Street, in Burtola, north Calcutta, on Sunday night. Police said local residents took the man to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, where he was pronounced dead.

 Subham Das, 65, committed suicide by consuming acid at his Beleghata Main Road residence on Sunday afternoon. Police said Subham?s family members took him to NRS Medical College and Hospital, where he died on Monday. He consumed acid reportedly after an altercation with his wife.

 Ultadanga police station will shift to its new address ? Block 13, CIT Scheme VII-M, Calcutta-67 ? on Saturday. The thana is now operating from P-177, CIT Scheme VII-M, Calcutta-54.

 The third-floor balcony of a three-storeyed house on BB Ganguly Street collapsed on Monday. No one was injured.

 Mithun Mondal, a Class V student of Blind Boys? Academy at Narendrapur, who committed suicide in his hostel on July 8, had been suffering from depression, school education minister Partha De said in the Assembly on Monday. An inquiry by the school authorities has revealed that poor vision, poverty and prolonged illness of his father had resulted in depression.

 The civic parks and gardens department on Monday filed an FIR against illegal felling of a roadside ashwatha tree in Golf Green. Mayoral council member Faiyaz Khan said illegal felling of trees has ?assumed an alarming proportion? in the Golf Green-Bijoygarh area.

